---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { Cpu, Briefcase, Code } from 'lucide-react';

const title = "BC PNP Calculator for Tech Workers & High-Demand Occupations (2026)";
const description = "Special guide for Tech, Healthcare, and Construction workers. See why your BC PNP score requirements are lower and how to qualify for targeted draws.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <header class="mb-12 text-center">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center justify-center p-3 bg-indigo-50 dark:bg-indigo-900/10 rounded-xl mb-6 text-indigo-600">
        <Cpu size={48} />
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">
        BC PNP for <span class="text-indigo-600">Tech & High-Demand</span> Workers
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        If you are an engineer, developer, nurse, or trade worker, the rules are different for you. In a good way.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      
      <h2>The "Targeted Draw" Advantage</h2>
      <p>
        In 2026, British Columbia drastically favors specific sectors. While a general administrative worker might need <strong>110+ points</strong> to get invited, a Software Engineer or Registered Nurse might only need <strong>80-90 points</strong>.
      </p>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 my-8">
        <div class="bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-900/20 p-6 rounded-xl border border-blue-100 dark:border-blue-800">
          <Code class="text-blue-600 mb-3" size={32} />
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold m-0 mb-2">BC PNP Tech</h3>
          <p class="text-sm m-0">35 specific tech NOCs. Draws happen almost every week. Faster processing.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-green-50 dark:bg-green-900/20 p-6 rounded-xl border border-green-100 dark:border-green-800">
          <Briefcase class="text-green-600 mb-3" size={32} />
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold m-0 mb-2">Healthcare</h3>
          <p class="text-sm m-0">Physicians, nurses, allied health. Often the lowest cut-off scores of all.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-orange-50 dark:bg-orange-900/20 p-6 rounded-xl border border-orange-100 dark:border-orange-800">
          <Briefcase class="text-orange-600 mb-3" size={32} />
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold m-0 mb-2">Construction</h3>
          <p class="text-sm m-0">Carpenters, plumbers, electricians. Critical for BC's housing goals.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>Top 10 High-Demand Tech NOCs (2026)</h2>
      <p>
        If your job offer falls under one of these codes, you are in the "Tech" stream. This means lower score cut-offs and faster invitations.
      </p>
      <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 my-8">
        <table class="min-w-full bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 text-sm">
            <thead class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900">
                <tr>
                    <th class="py-3 px-4 text-left font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">NOC Code</th>
                    <th class="py-3 px-4 text-left font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Job Title</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200 dark:divide-gray-700">
                <tr><td class="py-3 px-4">20012</td><td class="py-3 px-4">Computer and information systems managers</td></tr>
                <tr><td class="py-3 px-4">21231</td><td class="py-3 px-4">Software engineers and designers</td></tr>
                <tr><td class="py-3 px-4">21232</td><td class="py-3 px-4">Software developers and programmers</td></tr>
                <tr><td class="py-3 px-4">21230</td><td class="py-3 px-4">Computer systems developers and programmers</td></tr>
                <tr><td class="py-3 px-4">21234</td><td class="py-3 px-4">Web developers and programmers</td></tr>
                <tr><td class="py-3 px-4">21233</td><td class="py-3 px-4">Web designers</td></tr>
                <tr><td class="py-3 px-4">21211</td><td class="py-3 px-4">Data scientists</td></tr>
                <tr><td class="py-3 px-4">21223</td><td class="py-3 px-4">Database analysts and data administrators</td></tr>
                <tr><td class="py-3 px-4">21310</td><td class="py-3 px-4">Electrical and electronics engineers</td></tr>
                <tr><td class="py-3 px-4">22220</td><td class="py-3 px-4">Computer network technicians</td></tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2>How to Calculate Scores for Tech Jobs</h2>
      
      <h3>1. Wage is King for Tech</h3>
      <p>
        Tech salaries in Vancouver are high. If you are earning $80,000+, you are likely maximizing the <strong>Wage Points</strong> category in the calculator.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>$55.00/hr = Max points (55 points)</li>
        <li>Tech offers often exceed this, giving you a massive head start.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>2. Education Requirements</h3>
      <p>
        Most Tech stream applicants have a Bachelorâ€™s degree.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Bachelor's: 15 points</li>
        <li>Master's: 22 points</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        <em>Tip:</em> If you are a self-taught developer without a degree, you rely heavily on your <strong>wage</strong> and <strong>experience</strong> points. You strictly need that job offer.
      </p>

      <h2>Case Study: The "Software Engineer"</h2>
      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border-l-4 border-indigo-500 p-6 shadow-sm my-6">
        <h4 class="font-bold mb-2">Profile: Priya (NOC 21231)</h4>
        <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
          <li><strong>Job:</strong> Senior Developer in Vancouver</li>
          <li><strong>Wage:</strong> $60/hr ($115k/yr) -> <strong>Max Wage Points</strong></li>
          <li><strong>Experience:</strong> 5 Years -> <strong>Max Exp Points</strong></li>
          <li><strong>Education:</strong> Bachelor's</li>
          <li><strong>English:</strong> CLB 8</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="font-bold mt-4 text-green-600">Result: 115 Points (Invited in Tech Draw)</p>
      </div>

      <h2>Strategies for High-Demand Applicants</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Don't lowball your salary:</strong> If you are negotiating a job offer, aim for $55/hr as your "golden number" for max points.</li>
        <li><strong>Consider the startup scene:</strong> BC PNP Tech doesn't require the employer to have a specific LMIA in many cases, but the company must be established.</li>
        <li><strong>Look at Victoria:</strong> Vancouver has high tech wages, but Victoria has a growing tech hub (VIATEC) and offers <strong>Regional Points</strong> which Vancouver does not.</li>
      </ol>
      
      <div class="mt-12 p-8 bg-gray-900 rounded-3xl text-center text-white">
        <h3 class="text-white mb-4">Calculate your Tech Score</h3>
        <p class="mb-8 text-gray-300">See if you meet the cut-off for the next Tech Draw.</p>
        <a href="/" class="inline-block bg-indigo-600 hover:bg-indigo-700 text-white font-bold py-3 px-8 rounded-full transition-colors">
          Open Calculator
        </a>
      </div>

      <section class="mt-16 pt-12 border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Related Strategy Guides</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
            <a href="/articles/how-to-use-bc-pnp-calculator-2026" class="block group no-underline">
            <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 transition hover:shadow-lg hover:border-blue-500">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white group-hover:text-blue-600 mt-0">How to Use the Calculator</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-0">Step-by-step instructions for 2026.</p>
            </div>
          </a>
          <a href="/articles/bc-pnp-vs-crs-calculator" class="block group no-underline">
            <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 transition hover:shadow-lg hover:border-purple-500">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white group-hover:text-purple-600 mt-0">BC PNP vs CRS</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-0">Which system is right for you?</p>
            </div>
          </a>
          <a href="/articles/maximize-bc-pnp-score-tips" class="block group no-underline">
            <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 transition hover:shadow-lg hover:border-green-500">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white group-hover:text-green-600 mt-0">Maximize Your Score</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-0">Hidden points and Reddit strategies.</p>
            </div>
          </a>
          <a href="/articles/bc-pnp-calculator-faq" class="block group no-underline">
            <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 p-6 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 transition hover:shadow-lg hover:border-yellow-500">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white group-hover:text-yellow-600 mt-0">FAQ & Troubleshooting</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-0">Answers to common errors.</p>
            </div>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
